href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thermodynamicist\" title=\"Thermodynamicist\">thermodynamicist<\/a> famous for his work on an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Equation_of_state\" title=\"Equation of state\">equation of state<\/a> for gases and liquids.<\/p><p>His name is primarily associated with the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Van_der_Waals_equation\" title=\"Van der Waals equation\">van der Waals equation<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Equation_of_state\" title=\"Equation of state\">state<\/a> that describes the behavior of gases and their condensation to the liquid <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Phase_(matter)\" title=\"Phase (matter)\">phase<\/a>. His name is also associated with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Van_der_Waals_forces\" title=\"Van der Waals forces\" class=\"mw-redirect\">van der Waals forces<\/a> (forces between stable <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Molecules\" title=\"Molecules\" class=\"mw-redirect\">molecules<\/a>), with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Van_der_Waals_molecule\" title=\"Van der Waals molecule\">van der Waals molecules<\/a> (small molecular clusters bound by van der Waals forces), and with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Van_der_Waals_radius\" title=\"Van der Waals radius\">van der Waals radii<\/a> (sizes of molecules).<\/p><p>He became the first <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physics\" title=\"Physics\">physics<\/a> professor of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Amsterdam\" title=\"University of Amsterdam\">University of Amsterdam<\/a> when in 1877 the old Athenaeum was upgraded to Municipal University. Van der Waals won the 1910 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in physics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Prize in physics<\/a> for his work on the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Equation_of_state\" title=\"Equation of state\">equation of state<\/a> for gases and liquids.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Johannes_Diderik_van_der_Waals#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Johannes Diderik van der Waals","place_of_birth":"Leiden , Netherlands","place_of_death":"Amsterdam , Netherlands","text":"Johannes Diderik van der Waals , Physics, 1910","year":1910.0}